data.name: Spiced Turkey Stuffed Bell Peppers
data.quickTastyDescription: Savory bell peppers filled with spiced turkey and crisp celery for a delightful crunch!
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove the seeds and membranes. Set aside.
In a skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add diced onion and garlic, sauté until translucent.
Add ground turkey to the skillet, breaking it apart with a spatula. Cook until browned.
Stir in diced celery, cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper. Cook for an additional 5 minutes until celery is tender.
Fill each bell pepper with the turkey mixture, pressing down to pack it in. If desired, sprinkle cheddar cheese on top of each pepper.
Place stuffed peppers upright in a baking dish and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes. Remove foil and bake for an additional 10 minutes until the peppers are tender and cheese is bubbly.
Serve hot and enjoy your healthy, protein-packed meal!
data.detailedName: Savory Spiced Turkey Stuffed Bell Peppers
